## Finding Relevant Issues

### Search Patterns for Common Development Tasks

#### Profile & User Management Issues
```bash
# Search for profile-related issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai profile OR user OR account" --limit 10

# Search for edit/update functionality
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai edit OR update OR modify" --limit 10

# Search for data management issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai data OR dataset OR upload" --limit 10
```

#### Frontend Component Issues
```bash
# Search for UI/component issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai component OR UI OR interface" --limit 10

# Search for form-related issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai form OR input OR validation" --limit 10

# Search for modal/dialog issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai modal OR dialog OR popup" --limit 10
```

#### Feature-Specific Searches
```bash
# Map and geospatial issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai map OR geospatial OR coordinate" --limit 10

# File upload issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai upload OR file OR chunk" --limit 10

# Authentication issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai auth OR login OR permission" --limit 10
```

### Issue Analysis Workflow

#### Before Starting New Work
```bash
# 1. Check if similar issue exists
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai [your-keyword]" --limit 20

# 2. Check specific repository
gh api repos/deadwood-ai/deadtrees-frontend-react/issues | jq '.[] | {number, title, state}' | grep -i "keyword"

# 3. Get issue details if found
gh api repos/deadwood-ai/deadtrees-frontend-react/issues/[NUMBER] | jq '{title, body, state, assignees: [.assignees[].login], labels: [.labels[].name]}'
```

#### Issue Context Gathering
```bash
# Get issue with comments
gh api repos/deadwood-ai/deadtrees-frontend-react/issues/[NUMBER] | jq '{title, body, comments_url}'
gh api repos/deadwood-ai/deadtrees-frontend-react/issues/[NUMBER]/comments | jq '.[] | {author: .user.login, body, created_at}'

# Check related PRs
gh pr list --search "org:deadwood-ai [issue-number]" --limit 5

# Find linked issues
gh api repos/deadwood-ai/deadtrees-frontend-react/issues/[NUMBER]/timeline | jq '.[] | select(.event == "cross-referenced")'
```

### Advanced Issue Queries

#### By Status and Priority
```bash
# Open issues by repository
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai repo:deadtrees-frontend-react is:open" --limit 15

# Issues by label
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai label:enhancement" --limit 10
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai label:bug" --limit 10
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai label:frontend" --limit 10

# Recent activity
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai updated:>2024-01-01" --limit 15
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai created:>2024-06-01" --limit 10
```

#### By Assignee and Author
```bash
# Unassigned issues
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai no:assignee is:open" --limit 10

# Issues by specific author
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai author:username" --limit 10

# Issues assigned to specific person
gh issue list --search "org:deadwood-ai assignee:username" --limit 10
```

### Project Board Integration

#### Finding Issues in Project Boards
```bash
# Get all project items with status
gh project item-list 5 --owner deadwood-ai --format json | jq '.[] | {title, status, repository}'

# Filter by specific status
gh project item-list 5 --owner deadwood-ai --format json | jq '.[] | select(.status == "Todo") | {title, url}'

# Find issues by project column
gh project item-list 5 --owner deadwood-ai --format json | jq '.[] | select(.status == "In Progress") | {title, assignees}'
```

### Quick Reference Commands

#### Essential Issue Discovery
```bash
# Most common searches for development work
alias gh-profile="gh issue list --search 'org:deadwood-ai profile OR user' --limit 10"
alias gh-frontend="gh issue list --search 'org:deadwood-ai repo:deadtrees-frontend-react is:open' --limit 15"
alias gh-recent="gh issue list --search 'org:deadwood-ai updated:>$(date -d '7 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d)' --limit 10"
alias gh-unassigned="gh issue list --search 'org:deadwood-ai no:assignee is:open' --limit 10"
```

#### Context-Specific Searches
```bash
